@NODE "Intro"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Introduction
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    Where did I get the idea to write this "stupid" program? Mainly, from
    the old program LemOnWB available for AGA Amigas. It adds lemmings that
    run around on the wb screen, climb window-borders etc. I wanted
    something similiar for Amigas equipped with gfx cards, @{b}so CyberLemings
    was born@{ub}. @{"Here" link "CyberLemmings_grab.jpg/main"} is a small croped screenshot of it up and runing.

    CyberLemmings is basically the same idea as LemOnWB, but for gfx cards,
    and with the possibility of the user drawing his/her own graphics for
    their litle WB pet.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Reqs"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Requirements
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    * AmigaOS 3.0+ (and MorphOS, for the MOS version).

    * MC68020+ or compatible (PPC603+ or compatible for MOS version).

    * Some fast-memory.

    * CyberGraphics V41+ (or compatible).

    * 15Bit+ Workbench screen.

    * Enabled background/backdrop feature of Workbench/DOpus/(ScalOS).

    * AHI if sound is enabled. (Basically any version works ;))

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Feat"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Features
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    * Is "themeable".

    * Is system-friendly ;).
    
    * Supports images up to 256*256 in size.

    * Handles up to 256 frames for each animation type.

    * Supports climbers, diers, fallers, gliders, occupiers, pushers,
      teleporters and walkers.

    * Includes sound support.

    * Has numerous options to configure the appearance of CyberLemmings.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "History"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1.1 (2003-08-27)                        Public release #3         Major update
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    * Another bug in the stairwalk routine has been fixed.

    * Updated everything in the guide, and added some new stuff. Now, there
      is also a description on how sound support in CyberLemmings works.

    * Added support for a pusher "feature", also added a PUSHER tooltype
      that can be set in order to activate this.

    * Fix for offscreen-windows in MorphOS added, so windows can't be pushed
      of screen by the lemmings. (Would have been annoying ;))

    * Fixed the sound routines so that they use AHI instead of audio.device.

    * Fixed a nasty bug where characters sometimes could keep on walking
      after teleporting to a window.

    * Found a bug that could cause random enforcer hits in the teleport
      function.

    * Added Qweek gfxmap made by Nowee to the archive.

    * Characters now also teleport to the same window that they stand on.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1.1 BETA_1 (2002-01-14)                                           Major update
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    * GFXDIR now set to "PROGDIR:GfxMaps/" by default.

    * There was a small bug in the new stairwalk routine, fixed.

    * The background fetching of the new gfx-routines added in 1.0 could
      sometimes give heavy background corruption, especially if solid
      windowmoving was used. Changed back to the old background fetching now,
      thus loosing some speed in the cgfx routines.

    * Added sound support! Both the Lemmings and Worms2 gfx-set have
      included samples. Sound support can be enabled by setting
      the SOUND argument/tooltype. 

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1.0 (2002-01-10)                        Public release #2         Major update
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    * Lemmings can now walk in small "stairs" of stacked windows. They do
      do this when the "stair" is 1/4 in height of the current character.
      For the standard lemmings this would be 4 pixels max.

    * Oops! If there were NO collideable windows whatsoever opened on WB,
      the lemmings could fall thru the screen, fixed now! (Thanks Nowee!)

    * Did two things to lower the executable size, firstly I now use
      WriteChars/Printf() of dos.library/amiga.lib instead of the one in
      the C linker libs, I also disabled some things that the startup
      routine did that wasn't needed (68K).

    * The seed for the randomizer is now fetched from the current system
      time at each startup.

    * If the characters in the specified GFXMap can neither climb nor
      teleport themselves, the RANDOMDEATH feature is enabled automatically
      in order for the characters not to get stuck at the bottom of the
      screen. (This is true for the "Nudie" GFXMap.)

    * CyberLemmings threw mungwall-hits when flipping images if the images
      in the selected GFXMap didn't have the same width/height. Fixed.

    * Added a new gfx-set called "Nudie". (Try "GFX=Nudie".)

    * Added/removed some stuff forgotten in the guide, and fixed some typos.

    * Heavy cleanups of the internal code.

    * GFXDIR argument/tooltype added, so now you can place the CyberLemmings
      graphics anywhere you want.

    * Lemmings still showed one frame of the falling anim after climbing.
      Now finally fixed.

    * MorphOS version was not startable from Workbench, this was because of
      a faulty linker object (startup.o), this has now been replaced and
      fixed.

    * DONOTWAIT added.

    * Further optimizations to the gfx-draw routines, about 20% faster than
      in the previous version.

    * Fixed a small bug in the drawroutines that sometimes caused corrupt
      gfx when image-data used it's full width.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1.0 BETA_2 (2001-12-20)                 Public release #1         Major update
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    * ACTIVESCR option added, because lemmings do no longer animate if the WB
      screen is not currently the active one, if you always want it to move
      the lemmings, add this tooltype/argument.

    * Replaced WaitTOF() with WaitBOVP() and added a USEWTOF option.

    * Now requires AmigaOS 3.0 instead of 3.1.

    * LockLayer()/UnlockLayer() of Layers.library is now used while
      CyberLemmings draws to a Windows rastport.

    * Glider image implemented. (Umbrella lemming!)

    * CyberLemmings now exits if started twice.

    * X-Mas gfxset added! It is soon christmas, after all!

    * Worms2 gfxset added!

    * Small optimizations in the draw/undraw routines (around 20%
      faster now).

    * Teleporters implemented. If they can't climb they have to be able
      to move around the screen in some other way, right ;)?

    * "Occupied" feature added.

    * OCCUPIED and NOTELEPORT options added. So, now you can enable the
      occupied feature, or disable the teleport feature, if the GFXMap
      supports them.

    * No more left/right images, as it is just a waste of space...
      Instead only one image is suplied (with the character facing left),
      and CyberLemmings will flip them to the right internally.

    * Alot of new options added to the GFXMap.prefs file... Totally
      redesigned, now you can specify the following: Speed, SFrames,
      Frames, Offset and X. Amongst other things, that means GFXMaps don't
      have to support all images... For example: Worms have teleporters,
      but lemmings don't! ;)

    * When walking between two windows with the same height lemmings
      "flickered" and showed the "falling" image during one frame, this
      also occured when lemmings climbed up a window and reached the top.
      Fixed!

    * NOTITLEBAR option added. Before, lemmings did never collide with
      windows that had their border in the screen titlebar, now they do,
      unless this argument/tooltype is enabled!

    * Enforcer hits could occur when starting CyberLemmings from WB, this
      was because of a faulty linker library, fixed.

    * CyberLemmings could trash 1 byte of memory on some allocated
      images, this does no longer occur...

    * Major bug found... If all lemmings did not yet appear on screen,
      and the user quit CyberLemmings, enforcer hits occured.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1.0 BETA_1 (2001-06-27)                                           Minor update
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    * In some circumstances, lemmings could get stuck, when it was tight
      between a window/window or screen/window. Fixed!

    * Lemmings now somtimes explode (1/4 chance) when cimbing into a
      window.

    * Enforcer hit found, and removed!

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1.0 ALPHA_2 (2001-06-26)                                          Minor update
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    * malloc() replaced with AllocVec for better MorphOS compatibility.

    * IntuitionBase lock bug found and removed. (Hopefully.. ;)

    * Die image implemented.

    * Now lemmings dont "die" when climbing into a window...

    * Lemmings can no longer get stuck in the screenborders.

    * RANDOMDEATH feature added.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 1.0 ALPHA_1 (2001-06-25)                                         First version
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    * First (beta tester) version. Bugs and glitches galore, so
      beware! ;)

@ENDNODE

